{"name":"Wormwood","type":"vehicle","img":"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/art/vehicles/vehicle-water-galleon.webp","data":{"size":14,"scale":6,"classification":"","handling":-3,"cost":300000,"topspeed":"10 (5)","description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><strong>Masts:</strong> 4</p>\n<p><strong>Cargo Holds:</strong> 16</p>\n<p><strong>Notes: </strong>Square-rigged and fore-aft sails; true beast of the seas, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Heavy Armor}.</p>\n<p>Galleons come in a wide variety of sizes and designs. These ships all have one thing in common: they are huge, often having 3 or more decks, usually have catapults or ballista on deck, and have large castles mounted fore and aft so that their defenders can fire on enemy crews from above.</p>\n<p><strong>Weapons:</strong> Galleons can hold up to 12 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Ballista]{Ballista} in banks of 6 positioned on the port and starboard sides of the ship. In addition, up to 2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Catapult]{Catapults} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Ballista]{Ballista} may be positioned on the forecastle and sterncastle sides of the ship. These seige engines can be swiveled to fire out the sides of the ship or either forward or aft, depending on their position.</p>\n</div>","toughness":{"total":"20","armor":"4"},"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6,"ignored":0},"crew":{"required":{"value":"20","max":"20"},"optional":{"value":"40","max":"40"}},"driver":{"id":"","skill":"Boating","skillAlternative":""},"status":{"isOutOfControl":false,"isWrecked":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"maxCargo":16,"maxMods":0},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Galleon","displayName":0,"img":"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/art/vehicles/vehicle-water-galleon.webp","tint":null,"width":3,"height":3,"scale":1,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":false,"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"randomImg":false,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"zIMNBBFfdNnncDMc","name":"Ballista (x12)","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reload]{Reload} time is 5 minutes for a solo operator, or 2 minutes with a crew of 2.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A ballista is a mechanical engine designed to fire a massive crossbow bolt. One person can fire the device (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}). One person can reload, although it&rsquo;s faster with two people.</p>\n</div>","notes":"HW","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":500,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":true,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"3d6","range":"15/30/60","rof":"1","ap":"4","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/ballista.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"lIKUN2Xe9HwczqzA","name":"Catapult","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reload]{Reload} time is every 5 minutes with a crew of 4.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Catapults are simple devices that hurl large stones at enemy defenses or ranks of troops. They normally require a crew of eight to load the proje